      <link rel="stylesheet" href="7th.css">
  </head>
  <body>
      <h1>Example of Child Selector, Sibling Selector and Universal Selector</h1>
      <h3>The child selector is used to select all elements that are children of a specified element.
          In the example below the elements in the div tag will be affected  </h3>
      <div>
          <p>paragraph 1 in the div tag.</p>
          <p>paragraph 2 in the div tag.</p>
            <section>
              <p>paragraph 3 in the div tag.(inside section tag)</p> 
            </section>
          <p>paragraph 4 in the div tag.</p>  
      </div> 
      <p>paragraph 5 not in the div tag. it is just after div tag</p>
      <h3>The sibling selector is used to select element which is directly after another specific element.
          In the example above p tag directly after div tag will be affected. 
      </h3>
      <h3>Universal selector selects all the elements in the body. Here the font of all the elements is changed.</h3>
      <p>paragraph 6 not in the div tag.</p>   
  </body>
</html>

//css part

div > p{
    background-color: gold;
}
div + p{
    background-color: blue;
}
*{
    font-family: cursive;
}
